A man has trashed a $500,000 Ferrari with aims to impress his date.It is alleged that the 26 year old was trying to pace up with a convoy when he lost control as the road curved.According to au.news.yahoo.com a dashboardcam that is mounted on the vehicle recorded how the incident happened.&#8221; The driver was trying to keep pace with a convoy of luxury sports cars when he came to the easy bend that got the better of him,&#8221; au.news.yahoo.com reported.Both driver and passenger did not sustain any injuries but the $500,000 Italian car was damaged with the right section being ripped and the hood bent.&#8221; Entire front-right section was ripped apart and the hood was bent and buckled,&#8221;au.news.yahoo.com reported.TNA Reporter